Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the sweetcorn, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Stir only twice - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta{250%grams}, ~{3%minutes}.

Drain and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}.

Once the sweetcorn has charred, reduce the heat to medium-low.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @creme fraiche{75%grams} and @water{150%ml}.

Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and @honey{1%tbsp}. Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if needed.

Stir in the cooked pasta. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Serve in #bowls{}.

Enjoy!